Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[A classic vehicle for non-typhoid (and non-paratyphoid) salmonellae, eggs continue to play a part in this zoonosis. The risk of egg-related salmonellosis can be lessened at the source, and adequately cooking egg products and hand washing lowers risk at the "finish" -- in the kitchen. - Mod.LL

